In terminal:

docker run -d --name Sonarqube1 -p 9000:9000 sonarqube:latest


Now go to Chrome and search:
http://localhost:9000

Login using:
username: admin
password: admin
Change the password with a new one.
Then go to:
Project → Manually → Project Name → Project Key → Setup Locally → Administrator (My Account)
In the right corner, go to:

Security → Generate Token → Name → Type (User) → Copy Token

In Jenkins:
Login to Jenkins
Click New Item

Select Pipeline

Paste the pipeline given by sir

Then:

Check if the JDK and Maven name in the system tools are same or not.

If not, change it.
→ Go to Manage Jenkins → Tools → then check.

Then:

Check Sonar Scanner installation name — it should be the same as mentioned in the file given by sir.

If not, change it to match.

Then:

Check SonarQube name in Sonar Scanner configuration.

Then go to:

Manage Jenkins → Credentials → Global → Add Credentials


Choose Secret text

Paste the token you copied earlier

Save it

Then go to:

Manage Jenkins → System → SonarQube Installation

In Authentication, choose your created credentials.

Finally, run the build now.
